        public boolean isAllAdded()

 To check if all words are added, check trie.isAllAdded() to see if all characters are added;
        Returns:
        true if all words are added with the constructor, and false if one or more words are not added

      • getKeyValueNodes

        protected java.util.List<TrieNode<V>> getKeyValueNodes(java.lang.String word,
                                                       int substringLength)
        Equivalent to getKeyValueNodes(word.substring(0, maxLength)) for PrefixTrie, and equivalent to getKeyValueNodes(word.substring(word.length() - maxLength)) for SuffixTrie
        Parameters:
        word - : a word
        substringLength - : substring length of 'word' for prefix for PrefixTrie and suffix for SuffixTrie; for example, if word is "abcde" and substringLength is 3, then it's "abc" for PrefixTrie and "cde" for SuffixTrie
        Returns:
        the key-value nodes with level >= substringLength

      • getBestKeyValueNode

        protected TrieNode<V> getBestKeyValueNode(java.lang.String word,
                                          int substringLength)
        Equivalent to getBestKeyValueNode(word.substring(0, maxLength)) for PrefixTrie, and equivalent to getBestKeyValueNode(word.substring(word.length() - maxLength)) for SuffixTrie
        Parameters:
        word - : a word
        substringLength - : substring length of 'word' for prefix for PrefixTrie and suffix for SuffixTrie; for example, if word is "abcde" and substringLength is 3, then it's "abc" for PrefixTrie and "cde" for SuffixTrie
        Returns:
        the key-value node with the highest score among key-value nodes with level >= substringLength

      • getBestKeyValueNode

        public TrieNode<V> getBestKeyValueNode(java.lang.String word,
                                       java.util.Comparator<TrieNode<V>> comparator)
        Parameters:
        word - : prefix for PrefixTrie and suffix for SuffixTrie
        comparator - : a normal comparator 
         
 if a < b the comparator returns a negative value 
 if a == b the comparator returns 0 
 if a > b the comparator returns a positive value
        Returns:
        the best key-value node with level >= word.length();
